value.value: Skeletal element that forms superficially in the organism, usually in association with the ectoderm[VSAO].
Bone element that is adjacent to the notochord.
A parenchyma that is part of a lung.
A lobe of lung that is part of a left lung.

The semioval center is the white matter found underneath the grey matter on the surface of the cerebrum. The term is synonymous with cerebral white matter. The white matter, located in each hemisphere between the cerebral cortex and nuclei, as a whole has a semioval shape. It consists of cortical projection fibers, association fibers and cortical fibers.
One of the racemose glands in the walls of the esophagus that in humans are small and serve principally to lubricate the food but in some birds secrete a milky fluid on which the young are fed.
Either of the two neural nuclei within the habenula.
Four accumulations of gray substance embedded in the white substance of the cerebellum, comprising the nucleus dentatus, nucleus emboliformis, nucleus globosus, and nucleus fastigii.
System pertaining to blood vessels in the brain.
A zone of skin that is part of a dorsal thoracic segment of trunk.
Vein that drains left lung and returns blood to the heart.
Vein that drains right lung and returns blood to the heart.

A neural nucleus that is part of the solitary tract nuclear complex. The solitary tract and nucleus are structures in the brainstem that carry and receive visceral sensation and taste from the facial (VII), glossopharyngeal (IX) and vagus (X) cranial nerves. [WP,unvetted].
A gonad prior to differentiating into a definitive testis or ovary.

definition.value: typically part of the embryo - however, in male tammar wallabies the gonads are indifferent at the neonatal stage[8827321]

value.value: The adenohypophyseal placode forms the anterior lobe of the pituitary gland and gives rise to the endocrine secretory cells of the pituitary.
Rostralmost epibranchial placode. Associated with 1st branchial cleft.

definition.value: Taxonomic equivalence to EHDAA2 class made on basis of shared development: gives rise to geniculate ganglion

value.value: Epibranchial placode between geniculate and nodose. Associated with 2nd branchial cleft.

definition.value: Taxonomic equivalence to EHDAA2 class made on basis of shared development: gives rise to glossopharyngeal ganglion

A fold of tissue which extends into the peritoneal cavity of the developing embryo and participates in the separation of the pleural and peritoneal cavities.
A vein that is part of a craniocervical region.
Sum total of mesenchyme in the embryo.
A sphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.
A sphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.
Any suture between cranial and/or facial bones.
Any suture between facial bones.
Mesenchyme that is part of a medial nasal prominence.

The superior surface of the tongue divided by the sulcus terminalis into an anterior two-thirds, the presulcal part (pars presulcalis). and a posterior one-third, the postsulcal part (pars postsulcalis).
Mesenchyme that is part of a otic placode.
An ectoderm that is part of a buccopharyngeal membrane.
An endoderm that is part of a buccopharyngeal membrane.

An epithelium that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.
Anatomical region that surrounds the otic vesicle.
The embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the frontonasal region of the head.
Mesenchyme that is part of a developing hindgut.
An endoderm that is part of a anal region.
An epithelium that is part of a lateral lingual swelling.

A vascular plexus that is part of a right lung.

Subdivision of vertebral column that corresponds to the trunk of the body, containing the trunk/presacral vertebrae. In organisms that have a thoracic and lumbar distinction, this corresponds to the sum of both of these regions.
